hopobject.body: I'd like to pay this in, please best drugstore makeup of 2014 Williams and Bucs have spent a good amount of time trying to hash this out during the offseason so its good to see this taken care of. The deal ensures that the team's receiving nucleus (Williams and Vincent Jackson) will remain intact for the foreseeable future, with Williams coming off a solid 63-catch, nine-TD campaign in 2012 that saw him fall just shy (996) of joining the ranks of the NFL's 1,000-yard wideouts. While Jackson remains the team's top option at wideout, Williams' red zone ability, along with the Bucs' lack of proven receiver depth and pass-catching tight ends, should leave him with plenty of opportunities in his fourth season.
